===== 48VHPWR connector =====
In 2021, PCIe Card Electromechanical (CEM, pronounced like "chem" in "chemistry") Specification introduced a connector for 48 Volts with two current-carrying contacts and four sense pins. It was retained into PCIe-CEM 5.1 of 2023.<ref name="PCIe5.1 CEM">''PCI Express Card Electromechanical Specification Revision 5.1, Version 1.0'', 30 March 2023 – 10. PCI Express 48VHPWR Auxiliary Power Connector Definition</ref> The contacts are rated for 15 Amps continuous current. The 48VHPWR connector can carry 720 watts.

